House Resolution 822
By: Representative Hitchens of the 161st
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Sergeant Trey Nelson, recipient of the 2024 Officer of the Year award; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Sergeant Trey Nelson of the Dunwoody Police Department was recently named
4 the 2024 Officer of the Year by the Governor's Office of Highway Safety and the Metro
5 Atlanta Traffic Enforcement Network in recognition of his outstanding work combating
6 distracted and drunk driving; and
7 WHEREAS, Sergeant Nelson has served with the Dunwoody Police Department since 2010,
8 beginning his career in the patrol division and later serving as the department's community
9 outreach officer and public information officer before being promoted to the traffic division
10 as a sergeant; and
11 WHEREAS, in his current role, he plays a key leadership role in reducing distracted and
12 impaired driving through educational campaigns, targeted enforcement events, and
13 collaboration with external agencies; and
14 WHEREAS, his proactive work includes school zone speed enforcement, distracted driving
15 checks, and educating young drivers on the dangers of cell phone use while driving; and
